narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned specific terms and theories that helped me better understand relationship initiation, attraction, and communication.

Knowledge: all of the topics listed on the syllabus (it gives a very accurate run-down)
Skills: critiquing research methodology, applying psychology
I learned about how attraction and relationships work from a social science perspective!
I think because of the assignments my time management skills improved and so did my knowledge of social psychology.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths: Low stress environment, low workload, very engaging professor and lectures
Weaknesses: The lectures felt too long at times (2h 15 min 3x a week)

Strengths:
- interesting content
- fun instructor
- reasonable workload (about 1 hr lab and 1 hr reading between each MWF session in YSS)
- engaging activities (Monster Prom Videogame Assignment, Research Project, Open Literature Assignment)

Weaknesses:
- would have benefitted from more clear instructions on labs
- would have liked to know that I would need to cite studies for midterm/final on day 1
I loved how this course related to personal life, and I learned a lot that applies to every day life.
I wish there were more discussions so it could help apply our knowledge a bit more, but I enjoyed the lectures.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Sure, if you're looking for an easygoing intro psych course. The material is very, very accessible.

Yes, because of the strengths and weaknesses I listed: 

Strengths:
- interesting content
- passionate instructor
- reasonable workload (about 1 hr lab and 1 hr reading between each MWF session in YSS)
- engaging activities (Monster Prom Videogame Assignment, Research Project, Open Literature Assignment)

Weaknesses:
- would have benefitted from more clear instructions on labs
Yes for sure! A great professor and really interesting material.
